arts.ttl: Chelsea cruise past Twente as Bompastor maintains perfect start
arts.sum: Sonia Bompastor continued her 100 per cent record since taking charge at Chelsea as her side beat Twente 3-1 to secure a second Women's Champions League win of the season.

arts.ttl: Emma Hayes names USWNT roster for first matches since winning gold at the Olympics
arts.sum: Hayes included six players who could make their debut for the United States: midfielder Hal Hershfelt, defender Emily Sams, center back Eva Gaetino, defender Alyssa Malonson, forward Yazmeen Ryan and forward Emma Sears. Defenders: Emily Fox (Arsenal), Eva Gaetino (Paris Saint-Germain), Naomi Girma (San Diego Wave), Casey Krueger (Washington Spirit), Hailie Mace (Kansas City Current), Alyssa Malonson (Bay FC), Jenna Nighswonger (Gotham FC), Emily Sams (Orlando Pride), Emily Sonnett (Gotham FC)
